Here's how to implement all three in your `EditProductPage`:

**1 & 2. Intercept back navigation with a confirmation dialog**

Override `OnBackButtonPressed` (hardware/OS back) and handle Shell's nav bar back via `BackButtonBehavior`:

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    // Handles Android/hardware back button
    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            ShowConfirmationDialog();
            return true; // cancel navigation
        }
        return base.OnBackButtonPressed();
    }

    private async void ShowConfirmationDialog()
    {
        bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (leave)
        {
            _hasUnsavedChanges = false;
            await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
        }
    }
}
```

**3. Custom "Cancel" back button in Shell**

In your XAML, use `BackButtonBehavior` to replace the arrow with a "Cancel" button and route it through the same confirmation logic:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
             Title="Edit Product">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior
            TextOverride="Cancel"
            Command="{Binding BackCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- page content -->
</ContentPage>
```

Then in your view model (or code-behind):

```csharp
public ICommand BackCommand { get; }

public EditProductViewModel()
{
    BackCommand = new Command(async () =>
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool leave = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "Discard and go back?",
                "Discard", "Stay");
            if (!leave) return;
        }
        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    });
}
```

**Key points:**
- `OnBackButtonPressed` → handles Android/hardware back; return `true` to cancel.
- `BackButtonBehavior.Command` → replaces the Shell nav bar back button; set `TextOverride` for custom text.
- Both paths should funnel through the same confirmation logic, then call `GoToAsync("..")` to actually navigate back.
